{
  "stem": "753.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had place for Purim or for Hanukkah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had a wonderful teacher, which was unforgettable.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she was, like-- the way she was kept me alive mentally after, when I didn't go to school for many years.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was thinking often how she gave me in those four years more, more than called for and more than expected.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Her name was Mrs.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Schreistein.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I know that she died only a few year ago in an old-folks' home in Zagreb.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the Jewish holidays were kind of a strange thing in our family.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father belonged to a totally Reformed synagogue.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother, [LAUGHS] because of her brother and sisters, she belonged to an Orthodox synagogue.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So one day we went to the Orthodox, one day we went to the Reformed.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it didn't matter to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was religious for-- until I was nine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then listening to my sisters, who were very progressive and socialist, I decided I think this is better to be on their side.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in 1941, [SIGHS] everything changed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'd, I'd like to go back a little bit before we get into the war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Did you experience anti-Semitism growing up?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "None.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were-- we lived, as I said before, sheltered life, protected.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And going to-- not Hebrew, but we learned Hebrew in school-- to the Jewish school, there were only Jewish children in that school.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I-- practically, except my cousin who was half-Jewish and lived like a non-Jew, I didn't know anything about anti-Semitism except for they were talking in the house, in my home, about what's going on now in Austria and Poland.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my parents were listening to the radio.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were very scared.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
